t2762.text: If you’re looking for a likeminded community who have experienced narcissism, there are online forums on Reddit and Facebook. And, don’t forget you can check out Psychology Today, the Mayo Clinic and a whole host of other educational platforms to help. 10/

t2763.text: There are a lot of great online resources on narcissism. YouTube has a lot of PhD’s and life coaches that can explain what it is and things you can do to learn more and remedy the situation when you’re ready. 9/

t2764.text: The thing is, a lot of people don’t know about narcissism. People accept poor behaviour because that’s all they know. But if something doesn’t seem right, question it. 8/

t2765.text: Processing the events in the narcissistic relationship gives you the education so nobody EVER treats you that way EVER again. You also realise that it was never your fault - that you were manipulated by a master manipulator to suit their needs. 7/

t2766.text: When you begin to process what happened in the narcissistic relationship, you start to see clearly what the heck happened. You have an “ah ha!” moment and can pinpoint events within in the relationship that were totally out of line and abusive. 6/

t2767.text: When you leave a narcissist you realise that you’re stronger than you think - it just takes time to put all your broken pieces back together. Fog does lift. Talking helps. So does a lot of rest. You’ll have really good and really bad days. You’re processing loads. 5/

t2768.text: Other things I’ve learnt from leaving a narcissist: Nobody deserves to be treated like shit. This includes being lied to, any sort of gas lighting, put downs, manipulation, silent treatments, temper tantrums - the list goes on. 4/

t2769.text: The narcissist never really disappears. They will attempt to make contact multiple times for stupid stuff. Why? Because they want your energy. They need you to feed their narcissistic needs. 3/

t2770.text: When narcissists get desperate, they will do ANYTHING to win you back. This includes confessing to their emotional manulipation, gaslighting and blatant lying. They will even go as far as to hurt themselves to get you to come back to them. 2/

t2771.text: What I learnt from leaving a narcissist: They live on half truths or blatantly lie. They never tell the full story. They will always paint themselves the victim even after destroying you through gaslighting and manipulation. They will never acknowledge their destruction. 1/
